<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40147a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40147a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40147a"> 147(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ you hate God from / the beginning, / never know / religion until / after death, then / we are sure that / God sent the / Madhi </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Immediately before the battle of Tamai, Osman Digna sent a letter to the British, which read: <br>&ldquo;Know that the gracious God has sent his Madhi suddenly, who was expected, the looked-for messenger for the religious and against the infidels, so as to show the religion of God through him, and by him kill those that hate him&mdash;which has happened. <br>You, who never knew religion till after death, hate God from the beginning. Then we are sure that God and only God sent the Mahdi, so as to take away your property. And you know that since that time of our Lord Mahomed&apos;s coming. Pray to God and be converted. <br>There is nothing bnetween us but the sword, especially as the Mahdi has come to kill you and destroy you unless God wishes you to come to Islam. The Mahdi&apos;s sword be on your necks wherever you may go, and God&apos;s iron round your necks. <br>Do not think you are enough for us, and the Turks are only a little better than you. We will not leave your heads unless you become Mussulmans and listen to the Prophet and laws of God.&rdquo; <br>After the battle, a price of &pound;5,000 was set on Osman Digna&apos;s head. </mm> </dd></dl>
